DETERMINE DAM CLUSTERS
----

    Use 1-D DENSITY BASED CLUSTER ANALYSIS (DBSCAN), where TP_ID is the single 'spatial dimension'. Instead of using geographic coordinates, this uses distance along the stream line to search for clustering.
    
    Eps = 25
    Min(ClusterSize) = 1 dammed polygon.
    
    
    NOTE: 
      - NOT DOING EPS[optimal] approach. Test clustering using 25 and test clustering using 10; Make a call.
      - Median distance between nearest neighbors is 300-m. Thus, less than 300m could be considered 'closer than normal'; go with 250-m
      - At Eps=10 (100m search) just about every dam on WC is it's own cluster (155 dams, 126 clusters)
    
    
