IDENTIFY Anthro Dams/Reservoirs
----
<!---
    Reservoirs confound the potential effect of beaver dams on surface water by creating artificially flat open floodplains which allows LARGE amounts of water to pond. Additionally, active reservoirs are managed such that there is very little variation in SWA. Conditions experienced in these zones are not topographically or hydrologically consistent with the 'natural' stream conditions experienced in our study area. We want to compare beaver dammed to undammed **without** the potential influence of anthropogenic reservoirs.

    Reservoirs were identified using the National Wetland Inventory data in ArcGIS Pro. "Attribute" codes that end with 'h' are categorized as "dyked/impounded". If a riparian polygon was within 50m of a dyked/impounded NWI polygon, it is deemed 'affected' by the anthropogenic impoundment.
    
    All affected polygons are assigned "isAnthro = 1". This designation will be built into the dam clustering / sample reach delineation
